race.comment: OUR BLUE DIAMOND (1) could only manage to finish eighth at her latest appearance over 2050m at this track, a poor reflection on her short quote. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Big chance if her best form emerges. STRANIERO DEL MARE (6) had a win at this track two runs ago before finishing third at her latest appearance over 2100m at Bunbury, beaten 6 metres. Gets a soft run on the inside of the second line but may need luck at some point. Tackles a similar assignment and she can take this out. PARAGLIDER (4) ended last prep with a fourth at Gloucester Park over 1730m seven months ago. Capable of a forward showing while fresh. THE SLIPPERY DIP (2) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish second at this track over 2050m.
